    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-12-02T01:35:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-12-02T01:35:00-05:00" n="446"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d446">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">891.00/12–245: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Iran</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Murray</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tehran</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-12-02T10:00:00+03:25"
                            >December 2, 1945—10 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received December 3—7:25 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1041. Foreign Office has confirmed report published yesterday that all Soviet
                    military units still in Tehran have been withdrawn from city proper but says
                    they are encamped only few miles outside.</p>
                <p>Sent to Dept as 1041, repeated to Moscow 308, London 110.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Murray</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
